OL,3,CBoy, 15, becomes first person charged
OL,4,Cwith riot following nationwide disorder
OL,6,FA 15-year-old boy has become the first
OL,7,Fto be charged with the more serious
OL,8,Foffence of riot in relation to recent
OL,9,Funrest in England.
OL,11,FThe teenager, who cannot be named for
OL,12,Flegal reasons, appeared before South
OL,13,FTyneside Youth Court on Thursday where
OL,14,Fhe was not asked to enter a plea.
OL,16,FThe case was adjourned for two weeks.
OL,18,FRioting is an offence that carries a
OL,19,Fmaximum penalty of 10 years in prison
OL,20,F` double that of a charge of violent
OL,21,Fdisorder.
